Posted @withrepost • @dajanaydtonyo Being a Christian doesn’t excuse you from suffering 😮‍💨 #keepreading (this song has been echoing in my spirit for weeks)
.
If anything you suffer MORE but just not how the world suffers. We always talk about the blessings of God but I’m coming to understand that to suffer IS a privilege (hear me out lol).
.
Romans 5:3-5 says: “Not only that, but we rejoice in our sufferings, knowing that suffering produces endurance, and endurance produces character, and character produces hope, and hope does not put us to shame, because God’s love has been poured into our hearts through the Holy Spirit who has been given to us.”
.
Some of my lowest times in my life was when I had the greatest encounters with God. I was able to experience God’s love in a way I never had before. Suffering strengthened me. It showed me how to persevere and endure. It changed the way I prayed #fervent. No it’s not pretty or easy but when you are suffering with God on your side, it lessens the blow.
.
If you are in a season of suffering, hold on to that scripture and God for dear life. The worst thing you can do in this season is turn AWAY from God. Cry out to your Father. Let Him in on your pain. Then and only then will you see encounter God in a fresh way and begin see your situation through God’s eyes.
.
I love you with the love of Christ and I’m praying for you 💕
#dajanaydtonyo

TRANSPARENT TUESDAY: I just had a random thought of how blessed I am and as I’m thinking of the many ways I’m blessed I thought of the people who show up for me, unconditionally. My bestie/BFF/POC @southerncutie2 has been 10 toes down for me from DAY 1. If I’m rocking she rolling and vice-verse. Sometimes we laugh so much and so hard our faces hurt 🤣😅! We have literally NEVER HAD AN ARGUMENT or gone without speaking. EVER! And it’s not because we agree with each other all the time, because we don’t. We just have an immense ability to love and live and let live. People post so much on Beyoncé’s innanet and this app, most of it is not positive, I want to celebrate one of the most beautiful souls I know. No, it’s not her birthday, National BFF Day, or any other holiday we humans have designated as a day to celebrate anything. Here’s to continued laughter, dancing, crying, partying, celebrating each other’s milestones, lifting each other up, chasing our bags, creating and seizing opportunities ‼️Cheers 🥳 to you chica! And thank you for seeing me through some of my most difficult times and darkest hours all the while you love me without judgement.  Love ya, Ash 🤎✨
